title: For Sale:  M1 Carbine
postcontent: For sale a non-import M1 Carbine serial number 2041582 manufactured by Standard Products. Standard Products manufactured only 247,100 M1 Carbines during WWII, which is only 4% of total wartime M1 Carbine production which makes it relatively rare, just a few more than Rock-Ola. This carbine was manufactured between September 1943 and January 1944. It has an unmarked recoil plate. It has an Underwood barrel dated 9-43 and marked by a flaming bomb. The bore is bright and shiny. It has a second type milled rear sight by Hemphill. The trigger assembly is marked Rock-Ola. The stock has a cartouche of “NPM/FJA” for National Postage Meter with TN in the sling well and is in excellent condition. The oiler is an original in fine condition and is marked IN which is National Postage Meter. The sling is World War II type, probably Type II. The barrel band is type one with no bayonet lug.This Carbine comes with an original WWII 15-round blued magazine that is marked “KSG” on the spine, indicating it was manufactured by the Saginaw Company. The Magazine retains about 80% of the original blued finish.The photos show this carbine’s superb condition. This is your opportunity to acquire a rare World War II M1 Carbine in nearly immaculate condition.
